-- England Names Ravi Bopara in Squad for First South Africa Test
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-07-15T12:37:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-15/england-names-ravi-bopara-in-squad-for-first-south-africa-test.html
England named  Ravi Bopara  in a 13-
man squad for the first cricket Test against  South Africa ,
starting July 19 at the Oval in London. Jonny Bairstow was left
out.  The three-game Test series will continue with matches in
Leeds and London.  So far this summer, England has had 2-0 victories over the
West Indies in both Test and one-day series, as well as a
Twenty20 win. Then followed a 4-0 win against Australia in a
one-day series.  England squad: A.J. Strauss (Middlesex, capt.), J.M. Anderson,
(Lancashire), I.R. Bell (Warwickshire), R.S. Bopara (Essex),
T.T. Bresnan (Yorkshire), S.C.J. Broad (Nottinghamshire), A.N.
Cook (Essex), S.T. Finn (Middlesex), G. Onions (Durham), K.P.
Pietersen (Surrey), M.J. Prior (Sussex), G.P. Swann
(Nottinghamshire), I.J.L. Trott (Warwickshire)  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  